00:35:02.720 --> 00:35:07.990
Because when Muggsy was
at the camp, there were --

00:35:07.990 --> 00:35:11.010
he was not a national prospect.

00:35:11.010 --> 00:35:13.370
No one knew how good he was.

00:35:13.370 --> 00:35:16.660
And so there were a number
of point guards at the camp

00:35:16.660 --> 00:35:19.180 position:56%
that had these national reputations.

00:35:19.180 --> 00:35:21.030
So they would have a draft.

00:35:21.030 --> 00:35:24.690
And Bob Wade picked, because
of the numbers that got picked

00:35:24.690 --> 00:35:27.430
out of a hat, he picked
the worst center.

00:35:27.430 --> 00:35:30.650
And in lieu of that, he
was granted the first pick

00:35:30.650 --> 00:35:33.030 position:56%
of the best point guard in the camp.

00:35:33.030 --> 00:35:35.150
And he picked Muggsy.

00:35:35.150 --> 00:35:37.610
And Howard Garfinkel lost his mind.

00:35:37.610 --> 00:35:41.720
He said, sugar, you can't do
that, you can't take this kid,

00:35:41.720 --> 00:35:43.540
you got to pick the best guy.

00:35:43.540 --> 00:35:46.640
And he says, I did
pick the best guy.

00:35:46.640 --> 00:35:49.740
I know he plays for you in
Baltimore, but nobody's heard

00:35:49.740 --> 00:35:52.890
of him, he's a midget,
you can't take him.

00:35:52.890 --> 00:35:56.360
Wade said, I'm not only taking
him, but he's going to be my horse.

00:35:56.360 --> 00:35:59.930
And in Five-Star terminology,
a horse was --

00:35:59.930 --> 00:36:02.430
every player had to play
at least half the game,

00:36:02.430 --> 00:36:04.910
you could designate
one player as a horse

00:36:04.910 --> 00:36:07.160
that could play the whole game.

00:36:07.160 --> 00:36:08.690
And that was reserved for guys

00:36:08.690 --> 00:36:11.890
